Description:

This little projects starts a sumo simulation and exposes its data through a socket server.
In order to run the application sumo must be installed on your machine and has to be in the search path.

Get Sumo From here:
	http://www.dlr.de/ts/en/desktopdefault.aspx/tabid-9883/16931_read-41000/
	Arch Linux PKGBUILD: https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/sumo

Usage:
The application in its current state expects an Sumo project folder where all neccessary configuration 
files can be found and and a seed for the pseudorandom number generator. These values are passed by program arguments. 
For example:
	-p=Scenario/test/ -s=3
where "-p" is the absolute or relative path of the sumo project folder and "-s" the seed for the 
pseudorandom number generator.

Further Information:
You can learn how to use Sumo by reading their documentation.